295
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:18,080
Every single time

296
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:19,200
Just now

297
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:20,980
he took two oranges back

298
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,940
You say, of all things to steal

299
00:11:23,019 --> 00:11:24,759
he just has to steal oranges

300
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:26,799
Well, regarding stealing oranges

301
00:11:27,539 --> 00:11:29,740
it is well-documented in history

302
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:30,480
For example

303
00:11:30,659 --> 00:11:32,000
Lu Ji of the Three Kingdoms

304
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,700
at Yuan Shu's banquet

305
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:34,899
stole a few oranges

306
00:11:34,919 --> 00:11:35,559
to take back

307
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,000
to honor his mother

308
00:11:38,039 --> 00:11:39,840
Professor Fan, can you listen to me properly

309
00:11:39,899 --> 00:11:40,899
without interrupting?

310
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:43,299
I heard you mention stealing oranges

311
00:11:43,399 --> 00:11:44,659
so I thought of this classic story

312
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:46,000
Showing off your knowledge

313
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:47,220
Get out

314
00:11:47,940 --> 00:11:48,580
Listen properly

315
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:49,120
Okay

316
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:50,080
I'm leaving

317
00:11:50,139 --> 00:11:50,980
I'm leaving, alright

318
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:56,059
If you don't handle this matter

319
00:11:56,379 --> 00:11:57,700
Then starting tomorrow

320
00:11:57,799 --> 00:11:59,340
I'll start pocketing fruit too

321
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:01,419
I won't take those oranges

322
00:12:01,419 --> 00:12:02,840
I'll pick out the bananas

323
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:04,000
Fine

324
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:04,879
Auntie Cai

325
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,100
Don't worry, I'll definitely handle this well

326
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:08,059
Just rest assured

327
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:09,539
Can I rest assured?

328
00:12:10,299 --> 00:12:11,399
Just that old man Shan

329
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:14,059
Pulling a long face all day and never leaving his room

330
00:12:14,220 --> 00:12:15,700
And muttering away in there

331
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,539
Talking to himself, saying nasty things

332
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:18,500
Tell me

333
00:12:18,820 --> 00:12:20,559
Is he neurotic?

334
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:21,559
Look at what you're saying

335
00:12:21,559 --> 00:12:22,799
If he has an episode one day

336
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:23,460
And

337
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:24,519
Hits people or something

338
00:12:25,620 --> 00:12:27,519
Self-harm or hurting others shouldn't happen

339
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:29,600
Actually, regarding his situation

340
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:30,639
I have a basic understanding

341
00:12:31,279 --> 00:12:32,960
The old gentleman does indeed show signs of

342
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:34,240
Some sort of emotional disorder

343
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,500
I will find someone to resolve it

344
00:12:35,919 --> 00:12:36,759
According to

345
00:12:36,820 --> 00:12:38,639
Maslow's hierarchy of needs theory

346
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:40,419
And Freud's dream interpretation

347
00:12:40,799 --> 00:12:41,759
These reasons

348
00:12:41,759 --> 00:12:42,539
You talk too much

349
00:12:42,539 --> 00:12:43,480
I'll just listen to you

350
00:12:43,899 --> 00:12:45,480
Just get him sorted out soon

351
00:12:46,259 --> 00:12:48,139
Get that disorder of his sorted out

352
00:12:51,799 --> 00:12:53,840
Director Chang said he'd find someone to solve it

353
00:12:54,399 --> 00:12:56,340
He should have hired a psychologist

354
00:12:56,860 --> 00:12:58,399
I haven't heard of hiring a thief

355
00:12:58,919 --> 00:13:01,100
That's why I say you scholars have rigid minds

356
00:13:01,860 --> 00:13:03,159
Didn't I tell you?

357
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:05,559
I walked around with Uncle Shan for a long time

358
00:13:06,580 --> 00:13:07,980
He's not that "disordered" now

359
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:11,559
Looking left and right all over the community

360
00:13:11,580 --> 00:13:12,779
Wandering east and turning west

361
00:13:12,779 --> 00:13:14,240
Sitting here, standing there

362
00:13:15,259 --> 00:13:17,259
Although his legs aren't very nimble

363
00:13:18,519 --> 00:13:20,679
His gaze is piercing

364
00:13:21,620 --> 00:13:22,700
So I think

365
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:25,519
This is how Director Chang arranged it

366
00:13:26,179 --> 00:13:27,240
So

367
00:13:27,460 --> 00:13:29,279
We're asking you to pose as a thief

368
00:13:29,279 --> 00:13:31,100
To commit theft in the community

369
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:32,580
And lead everyone

370
00:13:32,759 --> 00:13:35,919
To the vicinity of Uncle Shan's residence

371
00:13:36,779 --> 00:13:37,559
Understood

372
00:13:38,679 --> 00:13:39,299
Why?

373
00:13:42,159 --> 00:13:44,240
That way Uncle Shan can see

374
00:13:44,340 --> 00:13:45,799
When an accident happens

375
00:13:45,879 --> 00:13:48,399
How much everyone cares for and protects him

376
00:13:48,980 --> 00:13:51,519
Let him feel everyone's warmth, and won't he

377
00:13:52,519 --> 00:13:54,700
Suddenly see the light?

378
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:59,419
Do I need to push Uncle Shan over?

379
00:14:00,059 --> 00:14:01,679
So everyone can take care of him?

380
00:14:02,039 --> 00:14:02,860
Good ide...

381
00:14:02,860 --> 00:14:03,899
No, that won't do

382
00:14:03,899 --> 00:14:04,679
Okay

383
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:06,299
After you're done

384
00:14:07,039 --> 00:14:08,200
You're a fresh face

385
00:14:08,279 --> 00:14:10,559
Remember to come back to me quickly

386
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:11,799
Don't worry

387
00:14:12,340 --> 00:14:13,460
At my place

388
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:16,019
No one will be able to find you

389
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:22,639
Well?

390
00:14:23,720 --> 00:14:24,379
You get it now, right?

391
00:14:24,860 --> 00:14:25,500
I get it.

392
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:27,980
I get that you're a self-righteous...

393
00:14:27,980 --> 00:14:29,460
...big muddle-head.

394
00:14:29,539 --> 00:14:30,179
How can you

395
00:14:31,279 --> 00:14:32,259
compliment someone like that?

396
00:14:32,940 --> 00:14:35,059
Do you have any common sense?

397
00:14:35,240 --> 00:14:37,440
If the thief was hired by Director Chang,

398
00:14:37,659 --> 00:14:39,620
wouldn't he warn everyone?

399
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:41,080
Just to help one person,

400
00:14:41,139 --> 00:14:42,379
he's stirred up the whole community

401
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:43,480
so there's no peace.

402
00:14:43,539 --> 00:14:45,220
Is this something a director should do?

403
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:46,299
That's why I say you...

404
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:47,460
...study dead books.

405
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:48,799
...read books to death.

406
00:14:49,139 --> 00:14:50,139
...read undying books.

407
00:14:50,139 --> 00:14:50,659
No.

408
00:14:50,899 --> 00:14:51,840
...die not reading books.

409
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,139
How does it go?

410
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:54,259
It's called mechanical studying.

411
00:14:54,259 --> 00:14:55,179
Reading without thinking.

412
00:14:55,220 --> 00:14:57,000
Better not to read than to read yourself to death.

413
00:14:58,019 --> 00:14:58,639
See?

414
00:14:59,139 --> 00:15:00,139
You said it yourself.

415
00:15:02,879 --> 00:15:04,360
I remember someone saying...

416
00:15:06,759 --> 00:15:08,179
There are four people tied to a track,

417
00:15:09,139 --> 00:15:10,659
and one person tied to the side track.

418
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:12,139
The train is coming.

419
00:15:12,559 --> 00:15:13,419
If you do nothing,

420
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:15,179
it kills the four people.

421
00:15:15,779 --> 00:15:16,700
If you switch the tracks,

422
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:18,320
you can save the four people,

423
00:15:18,460 --> 00:15:19,320
but kill the one person.

424
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:20,899
I told you that.

425
00:15:21,980 --> 00:15:23,360
It's called the trolley problem.

426
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,059
It belongs to the realm of philosophy.

427
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,159
In real life,

428
00:15:26,159 --> 00:15:27,159
would that work?

429
00:15:27,860 --> 00:15:29,200
Let's not guess blindly.

430
00:15:29,299 --> 00:15:31,200
We'll know if we ask Director Chang tomorrow.

431
00:15:31,259 --> 00:15:33,059
Ask then. Who's afraid of whom?

432
00:15:33,259 --> 00:15:35,159
If the thief was hired by Director Chang,

433
00:15:35,399 --> 00:15:36,340
what will you bet me?

434
00:15:36,860 --> 00:15:38,000
If I lose,

435
00:15:38,059 --> 00:15:39,700
I'll give you a hardcover edition of

436
00:15:39,759 --> 00:15:40,740
the Great Chinese Dictionary.

437
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:41,320
Get out.

438
00:15:41,460 --> 00:15:41,960
I don't want that.

439
00:15:43,679 --> 00:15:44,580
If you lose,

440
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:47,899
you treat me to a premium edition roast duck.

441
00:15:49,759 --> 00:15:50,799
If I lose,

442
00:15:51,279 --> 00:15:52,460
I'll treat you.

443
00:15:52,799 --> 00:15:53,340
Fine.

444
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:54,899
No matter who pays,

445
00:15:55,059 --> 00:15:56,519
I'm definitely eating that duck.

446
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:03,080
Director Chang.

447
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:05,399
Boss Li, Professor Fan.

448
00:16:07,659 --> 00:16:09,259
Do you two have business with me?

449
00:16:11,139 --> 00:16:12,899
We did have something to ask you,

450
00:16:13,580 --> 00:16:14,779
but seeing this gentleman...

451
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:16,379
This gentleman...

452
00:16:18,460 --> 00:16:19,779
You hired this gentleman, right?

453
00:16:20,799 --> 00:16:21,299
Yes.

454
00:16:22,399 --> 00:16:23,320
How did you know?

455
00:16:23,799 --> 00:16:25,059
Who am I?

456
00:16:25,799 --> 00:16:27,019
I could tell at a glance

457
00:16:27,019 --> 00:16:28,000
what was going on.

458
00:16:29,220 --> 00:16:30,360
Thin and small.

459
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,320
Must be agile.

460
00:16:34,399 --> 00:16:35,179
Where's the knife?

461
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:36,980
Where's it hanging?

462
00:16:37,460 --> 00:16:37,940
Knife?

463
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:39,460
No, I...

464
00:16:39,899 --> 00:16:40,399
I...

465
00:16:40,399 --> 00:16:41,059
I didn't bring a knife.

466
00:16:42,159 --> 00:16:42,840
Makes sense.

467
00:16:43,779 --> 00:16:45,240
Carrying that thing in broad daylight

468
00:16:45,299 --> 00:16:46,539
would easily reveal your identity.

469
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:48,799
Can you stop leading the witness?

470
00:16:49,019 --> 00:16:50,080
What?

471
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:51,399
Asking him about a knife...

472
00:16:52,159 --> 00:16:52,960
Professor Fan.

473
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:54,519
You still won't admit it?

474
00:16:55,820 --> 00:16:56,460
Director Chang.

475
00:16:57,299 --> 00:16:59,220
Tell Professor Fan about your plan.

476
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,940
You already know my plan?

477
00:17:02,679 --> 00:17:04,400
We are just about to go to Uncle Shan's

478
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:05,380
to execute the plan.

479
00:17:06,119 --> 00:17:06,579
Let's go.

480
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:07,640
Let's go together.

481
00:17:08,619 --> 00:17:09,900
We have plenty of time.

482
00:17:10,819 --> 00:17:11,220
Okay.

483
00:17:11,220 --> 00:17:11,759
Then...

484
00:17:11,759 --> 00:17:12,259
let's go.

485
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:12,779
Let's go.

486
00:17:26,299 --> 00:17:27,220
Who is it?

487
00:17:27,299 --> 00:17:28,220
Coming.

488
00:17:31,359 --> 00:17:32,119
Uncle Shan.

489
00:17:32,799 --> 00:17:34,460
I'm here with Boss Li and Professor Fan

490
00:17:34,460 --> 00:17:35,279
to see you.

491
00:17:36,420 --> 00:17:37,779
If you want to come, come.

492
00:17:38,019 --> 00:17:39,279
If you want to sit, sit.

493
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:41,299
I can't exactly

494
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,640
splash water and pave the road with yellow earth

495
00:17:43,640 --> 00:17:44,700
to welcome you, right?

496
00:17:48,460 --> 00:17:50,059
Wait a moment, I'll make tea for you.

497
00:17:50,140 --> 00:17:50,759
No need.

498
00:17:51,579 --> 00:17:52,660
We didn't come for tea.

499
00:17:53,259 --> 00:17:54,720
Not for tea.

500
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:56,299
Then what did you come for?

501
00:17:57,559 --> 00:17:58,779
If it's nothing,

502
00:17:58,920 --> 00:18:01,299
I'll give you two "mountains" stacked together.

503
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:02,339
How many of you?

504
00:18:03,019 --> 00:18:03,700
Please...

505
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:04,319
Get out.

506
00:18:06,380 --> 00:18:07,839
Don't kick us out, brother.

507
00:18:08,380 --> 00:18:09,119
We have business.

508
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:11,900
We brought the thief to you.

509
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:14,700
Why bring a thief to me?

510
00:18:15,099 --> 00:18:15,640
Take a look.

511
00:18:15,700 --> 00:18:16,160
Take a look.

512
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,160
What if you like him?

513
00:18:17,299 --> 00:18:17,660
Me?

514
00:18:17,660 --> 00:18:19,000
I like thieves?

515
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:19,720
Come.

516
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:21,099
Take a look.

517
00:18:24,220 --> 00:18:24,759
Dad.

518
00:18:26,359 --> 00:18:27,059
What's going on?

519
00:18:27,819 --> 00:18:28,519
Dad.

520
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:31,299
Don't be so polite.

521
00:18:33,319 --> 00:18:34,220
He's not a thief.

522
00:18:34,319 --> 00:18:35,160
It's his son.

523
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:39,119
This is your son?

524
00:18:40,859 --> 00:18:41,799
You are a thief.

525
00:18:42,740 --> 00:18:43,880
I am not your father.

526
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:44,880
Thief.

527
00:18:45,279 --> 00:18:46,900
Don't call him that.

528
00:18:47,140 --> 00:18:48,259
So he is a thief.

529
00:18:49,460 --> 00:18:50,240
He's not his son.

530
00:18:51,460 --> 00:18:52,680
Your son is a thief?

531
00:18:53,339 --> 00:18:53,819
Old Li.

532
00:18:53,819 --> 00:18:54,960
Let me ask.

533
00:18:55,519 --> 00:18:56,200
Uh...

534
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:58,200
Uncle Shan.

535
00:18:59,240 --> 00:19:00,680
Is he really your son?

536
00:19:03,079 --> 00:19:04,079
He is my son.

537
00:19:06,339 --> 00:19:07,900
But he is a thief.

538
00:19:08,900 --> 00:19:09,640
Yes.

539
00:19:09,839 --> 00:19:11,480
In our country's folk proverbs,

540
00:19:11,519 --> 00:19:13,200
there is indeed such a saying.

541
00:19:13,259 --> 00:19:15,380
It's called: Better a clever rogue than a foolish simpleton.

542
00:19:15,839 --> 00:19:16,039
And...

543
00:19:16,039 --> 00:19:17,839
Would you die if you didn't lecture?

544
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:20,519
Uncle Shan.

545
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:21,740
Tell us,

546
00:19:22,339 --> 00:19:23,559
what exactly is going on?

547
00:19:27,299 --> 00:19:28,259
This wayward son...

548
00:19:29,519 --> 00:19:30,819
lost his mom when he was little.

549
00:19:32,539 --> 00:19:35,059
But he was a sensible child.

550
00:19:36,900 --> 00:19:38,200
Morals, intellect, fitness, arts, and labor—

551
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:40,559
he was number one in everything.

552
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:42,819
Who would have thought,

553
00:19:43,259 --> 00:19:45,740
after college he joined a company,

554
00:19:47,619 --> 00:19:49,819
and a few years later committed economic crimes.

555
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:51,940
He went to jail.

556
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:58,359
Tell me, how could it not be a thief?

557
00:19:59,319 --> 00:19:59,940
Dad

558
00:20:01,619 --> 00:20:03,079
The facts of the case are clear

559
00:20:03,420 --> 00:20:05,539
I've turned over a new leaf

560
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:07,160
Give me a break

561
00:20:09,019 --> 00:20:10,200
If you hadn't gone to jail

562
00:20:10,759 --> 00:20:12,400
would you have changed for the better?

563
00:20:14,519 --> 00:20:15,700
You know

564
00:20:16,119 --> 00:20:17,400
when you went to jail

565
00:20:18,019 --> 00:20:19,299
your father, I

566
00:20:20,220 --> 00:20:22,099
almost died

567
00:20:24,460 --> 00:20:25,380
Actually, you

568
00:20:26,099 --> 00:20:27,319
don't need to be so sorrowful

569
00:20:27,819 --> 00:20:29,339
I'm not sorrowful

570
00:20:30,599 --> 00:20:31,779
He went to jail

571
00:20:32,299 --> 00:20:33,619
and I was home alone

572
00:20:34,539 --> 00:20:37,359
The gas fumes almost killed me

573
00:20:38,900 --> 00:20:41,380
If it weren't for my Loyal Dog Hachiko

574
00:20:42,019 --> 00:20:44,440
smashing the window to call for help

575
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:47,380
today

576
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:51,420
I wouldn't be here chatting with you all

577
00:20:52,700 --> 00:20:53,160
Dad

578
00:20:54,359 --> 00:20:55,259
it's all my fault

579
00:20:55,559 --> 00:20:57,259
What good does blaming you do?

580
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:00,759
That's why I always say

581
00:21:01,359 --> 00:21:02,200
humans

582
00:21:03,579 --> 00:21:04,759
aren't as good as animals

583
00:21:06,220 --> 00:21:07,240
You know

584
00:21:08,359 --> 00:21:11,299
you know your dad cares about his reputation

585
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,960
Ever since you went inside

586
00:21:16,740 --> 00:21:18,140
Among the neighbors

587
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:20,059
relatives and friends

588
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:22,279
and colleagues in the industry

589
00:21:23,779 --> 00:21:25,519
